<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Jenara</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-05 12:35:14</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The reason you didn't get another item is because you were given another Belt of the River. The belt is Lore, so the second one just disappeared.<BR>
<BR>
I got my smithing to 25, and the hay/oil combo is trivial for me already. I have done it three times, and haven't failed yet. You can get your smithing up to 25 just by sharpening rusty weapons if you don't have practices available (like me.) Note: Some rusty weapons trivialize before others. Rusty Two Randed Swords are hardest, as far as I can tell.<BR>
<BR>
Also, use a forge other than the one in Rivervale. It is a special forge for this quest. It doesn't check your skill in smithing, so a master smith will fail just as often as a person with 0 smithing. (At least this is the info I have gathered from a number of other boards related to this quest. Don't shoot me if I'm wrong.)<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps ya guys! Good luck!</font></td></tr></table>
